OL,3,CAirlines with low-cost reputations
OL,4,C'not always cheapest because of extras'
OL,6,FUnavoidable hidden charges for online
OL,7,Fconsumers ` or "drip pricing" ` is to
OL,8,Fbe banned under the Digital Markets,
OL,9,FCompetition and Consumers Bill
OL,10,Fprogressing through Parliament.
OL,12,FOptional extras are not included in
OL,13,Fthe legislation, but Which? believes
OL,14,Ffees for seat selection on flights
OL,15,Fshould be covered.
OL,17,FRory Boland, editor of magazine Which?
OL,18,FTravel, said: "It's easy to assume
OL,19,Fthat budget airlines like Ryanair and
OL,20,FWizz Air are always the cheapest
OL,21,Foption.
